<FILEID>AP-NR-04-19-88 0252EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BoxOffice     04-19 0445</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Box Office,0467</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>`Beetlejuice' Holds No. 1; `Emperor' Moves Into Top 10 For First
Time</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RICHARD DE ATLEY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ``Beetlejuice'' held on to No. 1 at the
nation's box offices last weekend, while ``The Last Emperor,''
which won nine Oscars last week, entered the top 10 for the first
time in its 21 weeks of release.
   ``Beetlejuice,'' starring Michael Keaton as a zany ghost that
exorcises unwanted people from homes, earned $7.1 million on 1,500
screens to keep its first place position for the third straight
week.
   ``Beetlejuice'' squeezed out ``Colors,'' which critics called
inflammatory because of its undiluted picture of gang violence in
Los Angeles.
   ``Colors'' earned $4.7 million on 422 screens for its debut week.
   The attacks on the movie and its defense by its director, Dennis
Hopper, gave it heavy publicity for nearly two weeks before it
opened Friday.
   ``Beetlejuice'' averaged $4,763 per screen while ``Colors''
$11,249.
   In third place was Neil Simon's autobiographical ``Biloxi
Blues,'' which earned $3.4 million.
   ``The Last Emperor,'' finished in fourth place last weekend,
with $3.3 million in ticket sales.
   In fifth place was Disney's ``The Man From Snowy River,'' which
earned more than $3 million in its debut week.
   ``Moonstruck,'' which won three Oscars, earned $2.9 million and
jumped from ninth to sixth place.
   In seventh place was ``The Seventh Sign,'' earning $2.7 million.
   ``Bad Dreams,'' about the haunting dreams of the only survivor
of a religious cult's mass suicide, earned $2.2 million for eighth
place.
   ``Good Morning, Vietnam'' grossed $2 million for ninth place,
followed by ``Bright Lights, Big City,'' which earned $1.8 million.
   Here are the top films as tallied by Exhibitor Relations Co.
with distributor, weekend gross, number of screens, average per
screen, total gross, number of weeks in release and, when
