<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Philippines-Bomb,0153</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Philippine Air Force Responsible For Bomb At Aquino Plantation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Philippine air force said one of
its F-5 jet planes accidentally dropped a practice bomb on a sugar
plantation owned by President Corazon Aquino's family.
   Initial reports blamed the U.S. Air Force for the incident on
Thursday, in which there were no casualties or damage. But a
Philippine air force statement issued late Monday said a Filipino
plane was responsible.
   Such bombs contain small amounts of explosives and spew out
smoke so pilots can determine how close the bombs come to targets
during practice runs.
   The statement said the bomb fell from one of three planes which
flew low over the Hacienda Luisita plantation during a training
exercise. The Philippine air force operates a bombing range near
the plantation north of Manila.
   The plantation is near the U.S.-run Clark Air Base.
</TEXT>
