<HEAD>Man Sentenced To 30 Days for Killing Kitten in Microwave Oven</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: The following may be offensive to readers</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man was sentenced to 30 days in jail for
killing his wife's kitten by cooking it in a microwave oven.
   George Jimenez, 26, of suburban Atwater, pleaded no contest to
one count of cruelty to animals in the Sept. 16 death of the cat.
   He was in a drunken rage when he killed the animal because his
wife went to a movie with a female friend, authorities said.
   In addition to the jail term, Jimenez was ordered Monday to
either pay a $150 fine or spend another five additional days in
jail and was placed on two years' probation.
   During the probation, Jimenez must undergo counseling and is
forbidden to harass his wife, said Deputy City Attorney Katherine
MacKenzie.
