<HEAD>Thunderstorms Bear Down On Southeast, Snow Forecast In Western
Mountains</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms rumbled across the Southeast today after
destroying several mobile homes in Georgia, while a winterlike
storm threatened to dump heavy snow in higher elevations of
California and Nevada.
   Severe thunderstorms that developed ahead of a cold front Monday
night spawned hail the size of golf balls and damaging winds in
Louisiana, Mississippi, Alabama and Georgia.
   The winds destroyed up to nine mobile homes west of Bainbridge,
Ga., Monday night, injuring three people, one seriously. The
sheriff's office said the wind left the homes in shreads.
   A major late-season storm was bearing down on northern
California, spreading rain across lower elevations and threatening
to bring heavy snow to the mountains.
   Winter storm warnings were in effect for the northern Sierra
Nevada range, the Mount Shasta area and northeastern California,
where more than a foot of snow was possible by sunset.
   In Nevada, a winter storm warning was issued for the Lake Tahoe
area with two to three feet of snow possible in the higher
elevations by tonight.
   The forecast for today called for scattered showers and
thunderstorms from the eastern Carolinas across Georgia and
northern Florida to the central Gulf Coast; scattered showers and
thunderstorms in California, with snow in the Sierra Nevadas; and
showers from Oregon to the northern Rockies.
   High temperatures were predicted to be in the 30s in upper
Michigan and western New York; in the 70s or 80s from southern
Atlantic states across the Gulf Coast, the southern Plains and New
Mexico; and in the 40s, 50s or 60s elsewhere.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 20
degrees at Fargo, N.D., to 76 at Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 60 showery; Boston 40 fair; Buffalo 32 snow;
Charleston, S.C. 64 showery; Cincinnati 38 partly cloudy; Cleveland
35 fair; Detroit 32 fair; Miami 73 fair; New York 42 fair;
Philadelphia 43 partly cloudy; Pittsburgh 32 fair; Portland, Maine,
41 foggy; Washington 45 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 24 fair; Chicago 39 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
45 fair; Denver 47 fair; Des Moines 39 fair; Indianapolis 33 fair;
Kansas City 38 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 32 fair; Nashville 43
cloudy; New Orleans 68 foggy; St. Louis 40 fair.
