<HEAD>Girl Struck By Lightning</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Tornado</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DOTHAN, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 9-year-old girl was injured by lightning
as she stood near a stove at her home during a storm, officials
said.
   Pat Bradley, deputy director of the Houston County Emergency
Managency Agency, said Shannon Jones of Cottonwood was hurt Monday
night when ``lightning hit a stove and then jumped to her.''
   ``She was knoocked down and there was a loud pop,'' Bradley
said. ``The girl's parents called the police, who notified medical
services and the girl was taken to the hospital.''
   He said the girl, who complained of pain in her side and a
headache, was taken to the Southeast Alabama Medical Center, where
she was treated and released.
   The lightning accompanied a tornado sighted by National Weather
Service radar moving southwest through south Houston County about
7:30 p.m., emergency officials said.
</TEXT>
