<1ST_LINE>r w BC-Attack-Chronology 1stLd-Writethru a0431 04-19 0433</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Attack-Chronology, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0431,420</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>Eds: Subs 6th graf pvs, _2:25 a.m., to make subs ``platform'' for
``platforms.''</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a chronology of events Monday in the
Persian Gulf as described by the Defense Department. All times are
Eastern Daylight Time.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   _1:01 a.m.: U.S. Central Command reports warning issued to
Sassan and Sirri oil platforms.
   _1:05 a.m.: U.S. Central Command reports Sassan abandoning
slowly.
   _1:17 a.m.: Commenced fire on Sassan, followed by ``check fire''
order to allow evacuation.
   _1:32 a.m.: Wainwright commences fire on Sirri.
   _2:25 a.m.: The Sirri platform complex reported neutralized.
   _2:39 a.m.: Marines aboard Sassan.
   _4:15 a.m.: USS Simpson's helicopter, in the vicinity of Sirri,
is fired on by three speedboats.
   _4:46 a.m.: U.S.-flagged ship, Willi Tide, reported under fire
in Mubarak oil field.
   _5:01 a.m.: An Iranian patrol boat closes to within 10 nautical
miles of the Wainwright; commander advises patrol boat to break off
course and stay away or be taken under fire.
   _5:15 a.m.: Wainwright orders patrol boat to abandon ship.
Patrol boat fires missile at Wainwright. Wainwright returns fire.
Patrol boat's missile misses. Simpson's helicopter reports smoke on
horizon. Simpson fires a missile.
   _5:52 a.m.: Wainwright engages two F-4's with standard
surface-to-air missiles.
   _6:10 a.m.: U.S. Central Command confirms successful missile
attack against patrol boat.
   _6:15 a.m.: Sassan platform neutralized by demolitions.
   _6:26 a.m.: Panamanian-flagged ship, Scan Bay, reported under
attack by Iranian helicopter near Mubarak oil field with 15
Americans aboard.
   _7:13 a.m.: U.S. Central Command reports patrol boat, identified
as the Joshan, has sunk.
   _7:26 a.m.: U.S. Central Command reports A-6 has attacked small
boats in Mubarak oil field. Damage assessment: one boghammer
destroyer; one disabled, one unknown.
   _7:59 a.m.: Iranian frigate Sahand receives multiple warnings to
turn back and not engage U.S. forces. Sahand ignores these warnings.
   _8:21 a.m.: Sahand fires on U.S. ships and aircraft. Boghammers
engaged again at Mubarak.
   _8:34 a.m.: First harpoon missile from an A-6 hits the Sahand.
   _8:41 a.m.: A-6's score direct hit on Sahand with laser-guided
bombs.
   _8:43 a.m.: A harpoon missile from the USS Strauss scores direct
hit on the Sahand.
   _9:06 a.m.: Damage assessment for Sahand: large hole starboard
side, listing heavily to starboard, superstructure in flames, life
boats in water.
   _10:17 a.m.: Iranian frigate Sabalan fires surface-to-surface
missile at the Strauss, Jack Williams and O'Brien and misses; also
fires a surface-to-air missile at A-6's overhead.
   _10:18 a.m.: Sabalan suffers a direct hit with a laser-guided
bomb fired by an A-6.
   _12:05 p.m.: Sabalan damage assessment: taking on water. down by
stern, two tugs attending, an oil slick at the fantail.
</TEXT>
