<2ND_LINE>PM-Federated,0169</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Campeau Expects to Have Federated Financing by Week's End</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CINCINNATI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Campeau Corp. says it expects to have
financing in place by week's end for its $6.6 billion purchase of
Federated Department Stores Inc.
   Campeau also announced Monday it has extended its tender offer
for all of Federated's shares until 5 p.m. April 28. Without the
renewal, Campeau's offer to pay $73.50 per share for all of
Federated's stock would have expired on Wednesday.
   Campeau, a Canadian development and retailing company based in
Toronto, has said its cost of purchasing Federated will actually be
$8.8 billion. That figure includes Campeau's financing costs and
the expense of the takeover battle it has waged since Jan. 25 for
Federated.
   Federated owns and operates more than 650 department, mass
merchandise and supermarket stores nationwide.
   Campeau, which purchased Allied Stores Corp. in 1986, has said
it plans to move some of Allied's executives from New York City to
Federated's current headquarters operation.
</TEXT>
