<HEAD>Monsanto Reports Record Earnings For First Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Monsanto Co. on Tuesday reported a 52 percent
increase in first quarter earnings due to increased demand for its
herbicide and other agricultural products.
   Net income for the three months ended March 31 was $210 million,
or $2.86 a share, on revenue of $2.13 billion. That compared with a
profit of $138 million, or $1.76 a share, and $1.87 billion in
