sale of its Alimet animal feed supplement and U.S. Environmental
Protection Agency approval of the use of Lasso MicroTech herbicide
on corn.
   NutrSweet, Electronic Materials and Fsher Controls also showed
improved sales and margins in the first quarter. Operating income
for Fisher Controls declined, however, because of higher raw
material and other manufacturing costs, Mahoney said.
